<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="130" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="129.[189,597,267,293]" box="[189,597,267,293]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,597,267,293]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,597,267,293]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Habitat and seasonal occurrence</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="129.[189,1110,313,405]" box="[189,1110,313,340]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">No data on habitat is know for this species, and it is only known from January.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="129.[189,1110,313,405]" box="[189,303,379,405]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,379,405]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="129.[189,1399,425,522]" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">
Currently, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2006" box="[320,417,426,452]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="goesi">
<emphasis box="[320,417,426,452]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">S. goesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[690,815,425,451]" name="Cambodia" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Cambodia</collectingCountry>
. However, its occurrence in 
<collectingCountry box="[1175,1294,425,451]" name="Singapore" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">Singapore</collectingCountry>
is quite possible. This species belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1965" box="[624,767,461,487]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divergens">
<emphasis box="[624,767,461,487]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">S. divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group and could is comparable to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shamshev &amp; Grootaert" authorityYear="2006" box="[1176,1346,461,487]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="130" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angkorensis">
<emphasis box="[1176,1346,461,487]" italics="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="130">S. angkorensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but distinguishable as given in the key.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
